# Environment variables for Webex BYODS Manager
# The sample uses token-config.json for local runs; for container/Lambda use
# these names as reference. In Lambda, store the equivalent JSON in AWS Secrets Manager.
#
# Required for token-config.json (serviceApp):
#   Service App ID (from Webex Developer Portal)
#   Service App Client ID
#   Service App Client Secret
#   Target Organization ID
#
# Required for token-config.json (tokenManager):
#   Personal Access Token (developer.webex.com) or OAuth integration token
#
# Optional for OAuth-based refresh (tokenManager):
#   OAuth Client ID (Integration client ID)
#   OAuth Client Secret (Integration client secret)
#   OAuth Refresh Token (from setup_oauth.py)
#
# Lambda-only:
#   DATA_SOURCE_ID=<data source UUID to extend>
#   SECRET_NAME=webex-byods-credentials
#   TOKEN_LIFETIME_MINUTES=1440
#   AWS_REGION=us-east-1
